Popular Nigerian Juju musician, Oluwashina Akanbi Peters popularly known as Sir Shina Peters, has been ordained a Bishop of the Cherubim and Seraphim Church. The legendary singer was ordained over the weekend at a ceremony in a Cherubim and Seraphim Church in the Iju area of Lagos State. The singer confirmed this on his Instagram page. Alongside a video and photo of his ordination, Shina Peters wrote: ‘‘Bishop with the swagger. God above all.” “To God be the glory. I will serve my God till the end.’’. The singer’s most recent music was a collaboration with Teni on her hit, ‘Jo’, released in December 2020. Shina Peters released his debut album ‘Ace (Afro-Juju Series 1), in 1989 and presently has 16 albums to his name. His first album which went double platinum gave his music career the breakthrough into the industry. ‘Shinamania’ produced by Laolu Akins was released in 1991, winning three awards at once with a Platinum Disc for selling more than 250,000 copies. —